Program-1
1] create a folder in a Desktop
2] Inside that folder open the git bash
3] git init
4] git config --global user.name "username"
5] git config --global user.email "email"
6] git config --global --list (it will Display user name and password If not go to credential Manager windows credentials remove the other user id present there)
7]  notepad file1.txt
    git add .
8] git status
9] git commit -m "v1" (keyword to save the code) message version. Create versions with editing in the Notepad
10] git log || show all the version with commit id.
11] git reset --hard "commit hash code" paste it here It will show you the data of the version which you have stored at particular version data
12] git push --set -u "repo url" -f

Program-2
1] create a folder
2] open that folder in vs code
3] Create a new file
4] Inside the file Print("Mysore")
5] open and save it in a .py (Python)
6] open a new terminal
7] commands to follow
8] git init
9] git status
10] git add .
11] git commit -m "test.py added"
12] git branch host1
13] git branch
14] git branch host2
15] git branch
16] git checkout host1 (Switched to host1)
17] add or delete one line in vs code
18]Print("VVCE")
19] git add .
20] git commit -m "VVCE is added"
21] git checkout host2 ("switched to host 2")
22] git add .
23] again the change or add the code print("vvce!")
24] git add .
25] git commit -m "vvce is added" (vvce is added)
26] git checkout master
27] git merge host1
28] git merge host2
‚úèÔ∏è Resolve it manually ‚Üí choose the final version you want:
print("Mysore")
print("VVCE")
print("vvce!")
Save file ‚Üí then run:
git add .
git commit -m "merged host1 and host2"
29] git diff
30] git clone "repo url" main

Create Pull Request
Go to GitHub ‚Üí your repo ‚Üí Compare & Pull Request ‚Üí Create Pull Request

Fork a public repository
Go to a GitHub public repo (example: https://github.com/<teacher-repo>/sample.git)
Click Fork ‚Üí your GitHub account will now have a copy.

Program 3 (B1)
JAVA
1] Create a folder
2] open in VS code
3] Create a new file Dockerfile
4] Inside Dockerfile
FROM openjdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY . /app
RUN javac Sample.java
CMD ["java", "Sample"]

5] Then create a Java file as Sample.java
public class Sample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Test");
    }
}

6] Then in CMD: Type
javac Sample.java
java Sample.java
or in vs terminal type
7] docker build -t name
8] in docker desktop got to images there you will find name1 click on run -> the java program will run or execute docker run java-app

HTML
new folder
new docker file and html file

10] Docker file:
FROM httpd:latest
COPY index.html /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/

11] Then create a HTML file
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Docker HTML Test</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from Dockerized HTML Page!</h1>
</body>
</html>

12] go to the Terminal
docker build -t name2
docker run -d -P 8001:80 name2

-d ‚Üí runs in background
-p 8001:80 ‚Üí maps local port 8001 to container‚Äôs port 80

to check visit: http://localhost:8001/

Program 4 (B2)
1] Continue with the B1 program and then add the two Comand in the terminal
docker tag hi:latest username/hi:v1 //tag=hi
docker push username/hi:v1 
docker pull username/hi:vi

üê¨ B2 ‚Äî Dockerize MySQL Database and demonstrate client-server
üéØ Objective

To demonstrate MySQL server and client model using Docker containers.

üß† Steps

Pull MySQL image

docker pull mysql:latest


Run MySQL container

docker run --name mysql-server -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root -d mysql:latest


Verify running container

docker ps


Run MySQL client

docker exec -it mysql-server mysql -uroot -p


(Password: root)

Inside MySQL shell

CREATE DATABASE demo;
USE demo;
CREATE TABLE student (id INT, name VARCHAR(20));
INSERT INTO student VALUES (1, 'Vishal'), (2, 'Shenoy');
SELECT * FROM student;


‚úÖ Output: Shows data entered in table.

Exit MySQL shell

exit


‚úÖ Result: MySQL container created, and client-server communication established using Docker.
